=== DATASET OVERVIEW ===
This dataset supports acquisition analytics for credit card applications and approvals.

It tracks application creation, approval decisions, inbound and outbound acquisition channels, and client product codes.

The dataset is used for monitoring application volumes, approval performance, and channel effectiveness.

Primary business analysis areas:
• Application volume trends
• Account approval performance
• Channel acquisition performance
• Product segment performance
• Month-over-month and year-over-year growth analysis


=== DATA GRAIN ===
Each row in the acquisition_semantic_data table represents one completed application record.

Other tables contain supporting dimensions for acquisition channels and product codes.


=== TABLES ===
[asd] Acquisition_semantic_data  
Completed application transactions.  
Grain: 1 row = 1 application record.

[ibc] inbound_channels  
Inbound acquisition channel definitions.  
Grain: 1 row = 1 inbound channel.

[obc] outbound_channels  
Outbound acquisition channel definitions.  
Grain: 1 row = 1 outbound channel.

[cpc] cpc  
Client product code information.  
Grain: 1 row = 1 CPC.


=== PRIMARY METRICS ===

application_count
Definition: Total number of applications submitted.
Calculation: count(appl_id)
Unit: count

account_count
Definition: Total number of approved applications converted into accounts.
Calculation: count(appl_id where application_status = 'A')
Unit: count

approval_rate
Definition: Percentage of approved accounts relative to total applications.
Calculation: sum(account_count) / sum(application_count)
Unit: percentage


=== NAMING CONVENTIONS ===
*_id → unique identifier
*_count → aggregated count metric
*_date → date field
*_rate → calculated percentage metric

Channel tables represent acquisition source attributes.


=== GLOSSARY ===
Application_count  
Count of submitted credit card applications.

Account_count  
Count of applications that were approved and converted to accounts.

Approval_rate  
Approval ratio calculated as approved accounts divided by total applications.


=== TIME DIMENSIONS ===

application_creation_date  
Date the application was submitted.

system_decision_date  
Date the approval or rejection decision was made.

Date table should be used for time-series analysis.


=== DIMENSIONS ===

Inbound Channel  
Channel through which the application originated from inbound sources.

Outbound Channel  
Channel through which the application originated from outbound campaigns.

Client Product Code (CPC)  
Product or card segment associated with the application.


=== CALCULATION GUIDANCE ===

Year-to-Date Application Count
Count of applications where application_creation_date falls within the current year up to today's date.

Year-to-Date Approval Rate
sum(account_count) / sum(application_count) for the current year.

Last Month Approval Rate
Calculate approval rate using applications where system_decision_date falls in the previous month.

Month-over-Month Account Change
(current_month_account_count − previous_month_account_count) / previous_month_account_count

Year-over-Year Growth
(current_year_application_count / last_year_application_count) − 1


=== DATA CHARACTERISTICS ===
• Each application is represented once in the acquisition dataset.
• Approval status determines whether an application becomes an account.
• Date table should be used for all calendar-based filtering.


=== COMMON BUSINESS QUESTIONS ===

Year-to-Date application count.

Year-to-Date approval rate.

Last month approval rate.

Month-over-month change in account approvals.

Which product segment had the highest number of applications last month?

Which segment has the highest approval rate?

Which acquisition channels generate the highest applications?


=== RESPONSE GUIDELINES ===
When answering questions:

Trend analysis → return metric values and compare previous period.

Ranking questions → return top segments or channels sorted by metric.

Approval analysis → calculate approval_rate using account_count / application_count.

Growth questions → compute percent change between time periods.


=== DEFAULT ANALYSIS RULES ===

If timeframe is not specified → assume most recent full month.

For trend analysis → use application_creation_date.

For approval metrics → use system_decision_date.

For segmentation → use CPC or acquisition channel.


=== DATA PRIVACY ===
This dataset contains aggregated application analytics only.

No personally identifiable information should be exposed in responses.


=== MODEL EXTENSIBILITY ===
Future metrics should be added in the PRIMARY METRICS section.

Future acquisition channels or product segments will follow the same naming conventions.
